char.comment: U+03DB is the modern Greek symbol for 6, but as a recent addition to Unicode, it displaced 03DA, which it treats as a capital, though 03DA is more widely found in fonts. Hence 03DB is here set to display as 03DA. Use 03DB for numeric use if shape is vaguely like final sigma or cursive s-t ligature (origin of the name stigma). If form is like digamma or like upper half of box (gamma facing mirror gamma), use small digamma (diggr).

Hence 03DB is here set to display as 03DA. Use 03DB for numeric use if shape is vaguely like final sigma or cursive s-t ligature (origin of the name stigma). If form is like digamma or like upper half of box (gamma facing mirror gamma), use small digamma (diggr).
